Volatility
Memory forensics framework

Forensics
Description
Volatility is an advanced memory forensics framework for analyzing RAM dumps. It can extract running processes, network connections, registry hives, and malware artifacts from memory images.

Installation / Check
Check if installed:

which volatility
Install command:

sudo apt install volatility
Basic Syntax
volatility -f <memory_dump> <plugin>
Common Commands
Command	What it does	When to use	Risk
volatility -f memory.raw imageinfo

Identify profile	First step - determine OS profile	
volatility -f memory.raw --profile=Win7SP1x64 pslist

List processes	See running processes	
volatility -f memory.raw --profile=Win7SP1x64 netscan

Network connections	Find network activity	
volatility -f memory.raw --profile=Win7SP1x64 hashdump

Dump hashes	Extract password hashes	
volatility -f memory.raw --profile=Win7SP1x64 malfind

Find malware	Detect injected code	
Step-by-Step Guide
1
Obtain memory dump
2
Run imageinfo to find profile
3
List processes with pslist
4
Check network with netscan
5
Look for malware with malfind
6
Extract specific artifacts
Understanding the Output
Output shows processes, PIDs, memory addresses, network connections. Each plugin has specific output format.

Important Warnings
•
Requires correct profile selection
•
Memory analysis is complex
•
Some plugins require symbols
•
Large dumps need significant RAM
⚠️ Use Kali Linux tools only on systems you own or have written permission to test. Unauthorized hacking is illegal and can result in criminal charges.
